<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB8FFD4FE02FED1FD44FE15" authorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Buerki, Callm., Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[427,644,375,399]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Lepidocupania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glabra">Lepidocupania glabra</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is endemic to the Tontouta River valley (Grande Terre). It is found in maquis and continuous tall maquis (“maquis paraforestier”, see 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB8FFD4FF31FE71FEA3FE75" author="MCCOY, S. G. &amp; JAFFRE, F." box="[152,355,471,495]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" pagination="579 - 594" refId="ref12158" refString="MCCOY, S. G., T. JAFFRE, F. RIGAULT &amp; J. E. ASH (1999). Fire and succession in the ultramafic maquis of New Caledonia. J. Biogeog. 26: 579 - 594." type="journal article" year="1999">MCCOY et al., 1999</bibRefCitation>
for details) dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB8FFD4FDD1FE71FDE8FD95" authority="(J. Poiss.) L. A. S. Johnson" authorityName="L. A. S. Johnson" baseAuthorityName="J. Poiss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Gymnostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chamaecyparis">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB8FFD4FDD1FE71FEC3FD95" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Gymnostoma chamaecyparis</emphasis>
(J. Poiss.) L.A.S. Johnson
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB8FFD4FD90FE51FD0FFD94" box="[569,719,503,526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Casuarinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB8FFD4FD90FE51FD0FFD94" box="[569,719,503,526]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Casuarinaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) on ultramafic substrate, primarily alluvium, between 20 and 
<quantity id="9E0122BAFFB8FFD4FFD8FD91FF76FDD4" box="[113,182,567,591]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB8FFD4FF6FFD91FE95FDD5" author="ADEMA, F." box="[198,341,567,591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" refId="ref11451" refString="ADEMA, F. (1991). Cupaniopsis Radlk. (Sapindaceae): a monograph. Leiden Bot. Ser. 15." type="book" year="1991">ADEMA, 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB8FFD4FEC9FD91FDD5FDD5" author="D'ANGELO, S." box="[352,533,567,591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" refId="ref11926" refString="D'ANGELO, S. (2017). Ecologie et conservation de trois especes rares et menacees de Nouvelle-Caledonie. Memoire de Master. Universite de Lorraine-UMR ECOFOG, Kourou &amp; IAC, Paita." type="book" year="2017">D'ANGELO, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="11E3DCD4FFB8FFD4FF3EFDDEFF77FD75" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="59468F5FFFB8FFD4FF3EFDDEFF77FD75" blockId="7.[113,766,631,751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB8FFD4FF3EFDDEFF2AFD15" box="[151,234,632,655]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="276">Notes. –</emphasis>
This species has been assigned an IUCN risk of extinction status of “Critically Endangered” [CR] based on its narrow distribution and reduction in population size (
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB8FFD4FD06FD11FF6BFD75" author="IUCN" pageId="7" pageNumber="276" refId="ref12093" refString="IUCN (2020). The IUCN Red List of threatened species. [https: // www. iucnredlist. org]" type="url" year="2020">IUCN, 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
